In this step, I created all the required accounts that I will use throughout the project. These platforms help with version control, cloud services, backend setup, and AI tasks.

A.Creating a GitHub Account

1.Go to https://github.com/
2.Click Sign up
3.Enter whatever personal information will be asked 
4.Create account
Log in and set up your profile
â†’ Now you can create repositories and push your code.

B.Creating a Google Cloud Account (for Firebase & Cloud Run)

1.Visit https://cloud.google.com/
2.Click Get Started for Free(google cloud can deduct 1 ruppee or it might be free depends)
3.Sign in with your Google account email id 
After setup:
Open Google Cloud Console
You can access Firebase, Cloud Run, and other services.

C.Creating a Supabase Account

1.Go to https://supabase.com/
2.Click Start your project
3.Sign in using GitHub or email
4.Create a new project inside the dashboard
5.Supabase is now ready for database and authentication tasks.

D.Creating a Hugging Face Account

1.Visit https://huggingface.co/
Create an account using email or GitHub login

Now you can access models, datasets, and create API tokens.
